{
  "text": "KIDSCREEN-52 quality-of-life measure for children and adolescents (KIDSCREEN-52 HRQOL) was funded by the European Commission and developed as a self-report measure applicable to healthy and chronically ill children and adolescents eight to eighteen years of age. Various psychometric aspects of the KIDSCREEN-52-HRQOL had been studied by Ravens-Sieberer et al. in 12 European countries [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
